2:T471,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes","description":"Discover underground motors for period London homes. Learn how they work silently beneath heritage properties, solve noise and vibration issues, and preserve architectural integrity with seamless modern functionality. Elevate your home today.","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/underground-gate-motors-london/","datePublished":"2026-03-17","dateModified":"2026-03-17","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk","width":1200,"height":630},"author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/android-chrome-512x512.png","width":512,"height":512}},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/underground-gate-motors-london/"}}5:["slug","underground-gate-motors-london","d"]
0:["0zc25QUguIxWkQeMj7sNy",[[["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","underground-gate-motors-london","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__?{\"slug\":\"underground-gate-motors-london\"}",{}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["blog",{"children":[["slug","underground-gate-motors-london","d"],{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$2"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Blog\",\"item\":\"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes\",\"item\":\"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/blog/underground-gate-motors-london/\"}]}"}}],["$","$L3",null,{"article":{"slug":"underground-gate-motors-london","relatedServiceSlug":"electric-swing-gates","title":"Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes","metaTitle":"Underground Motors: Discreet Automation for London Period Homes","metaDescription":"Discover underground motors for period London homes. Learn how they work silently beneath heritage properties, solve noise and vibration issues, and preserve architectural integrity with seamless modern functionality. Elevate your home today.","category":"Automation","publishDate":"2026-03-17","featuredImage":"","excerpt":"Underground motors enable silent automation in period homes by installing compact, low-noise actuators beneath floorboards or in basements, powering systems like automated blinds and curtains without ...","content":[{"type":"h2","text":"Understanding Underground Motors"},{"type":"p","text":"Underground motors enable silent automation in period homes by installing compact, low-noise actuators beneath floorboards or in basements, powering systems like automated blinds and curtains without visible hardware. These concealed DC brushless motors, typically operating at 12-24V and 5-50W, fit seamlessly into subfloors or cavity walls of historic buildings. Common applications include automated blinds, gates, and lifts in Victorian homes and Georgian architecture."},{"type":"p","text":"Key features make them ideal for discreet automation in London townhouses. An IP65 rating ensures weatherproof protection for basement installations, while noise levels stay below 30dB for quiet operation. This preserves the historical authenticity of listed buildings in conservation areas."},{"type":"p","text":"Experts recommend underground motors for period property retrofits because they support smart home automation with wireless controls. Integration with Zigbee hubs or Z-Wave devices allows app-controlled devices and voice-activated systems. Homeowners enjoy modern convenience without compromising architectural preservation."},{"type":"p","text":"For luxury automation in Edwardian properties, these energy-efficient motors offer zoned automation and multi-room control. Professional installation by certified electricians ensures compliance with building regulations and heritage compliance. This approach delivers seamless integration of invisible technology."},{"type":"h3","text":"How They Work Beneath Period Homes"},{"type":"p","text":"Underground motors use gear-driven linear actuators like Somfy's LT50 series, buried 10-20cm below Georgian floorboards, connected via low-voltage wiring to Zigbee hubs for app control. The core setup relies on three main components for reliable performance in heritage houses. This hidden mechanism powers automated curtains and smart shading without surface disruption."},{"type":"p","text":"First, the motor itself is a 24V brushless unit delivering 10Nm torque, ideal for lifting heavy fabrics in Victorian townhouses. It features vibration dampening to avoid disturbing original structures. Compact design fits into tight underfloor systems or cavity walls."},{"type":"p","text":"Second, the drive system employs rack-and-pinion mechanisms for precise blind movement, often paired with steel cables for durability. In a real example, a Victorian townhouse retrofitted with 4x underfloor blind motors controls 12m² windows across multiple rooms. This setup includes thermal insulation to protect against dampness in London basements."},{"type":"p","text":"Third, control systems like Z-Wave relays in the basement enable HomeKit integration, Google Home compatible setups, or Alexa skills. A simple diagram shows the motor linked to a central hub via concealed wiring, with discreet sensors for motion detection. Professional installation ensures maintenance-free systems with long-life batteries for battery-powered actuators."},{"type":"h2","text":"Challenges of Traditional Automation in Heritage Properties"},{"type":"p","text":"Traditional surface-mounted motors disrupt heritage aesthetics and violate UK conservation guidelines, creating visible scarring on period cornices and generating noise that disturbs listed building authenticity. In period London homes, such as Victorian townhouses and Georgian architecture, these installations often clash with historical features. English Heritage guidelines prohibit visible modern fixtures on Grade II* properties, making discreet solutions essential."},{"type":"p","text":"Aesthetic damage occurs when brackets and tracks mar delicate mouldings or expose wiring on ornate ceilings. Homeowners in conservation areas face rejection from planning authorities for such alterations. This pushes owners towards underground motors and hidden mechanisms to preserve architectural integrity."},{"type":"p","text":"Regulatory violations arise from non-compliant retrofits that fail heritage compliance checks. Acoustic issues compound the problem, as humming motors echo through thin walls of Edwardian properties. These challenges highlight the need for discreet automation that integrates seamlessly without compromising historical authenticity."},{"type":"p","text":"The primary technical hurdle lies in controlling noise and vibration, which demands specialised engineering for period property retrofits. Surface systems simply cannot meet the silence required in luxury heritage houses."},{"type":"h3","text":"Noise and Vibration Issues"},{"type":"p","text":"Standard motors produce noise at conversation levels with vibrations that risk cracking age-old plaster in historic buildings. These disturbances travel through timber joists, undermining the quiet charm of London townhouses. Experts recommend addressing this core issue for successful smart home automation."},{"type":"p","text":"Key problems include AC motor hum, gear whine transmission through joists, harmonic vibration that affects lime plaster, and thermal expansion noise. In Victorian homes, such vibrations loosen fragile cornices over time. Discreet automation counters this with targeted fixes."},{"type":"p","text":"Solutions start with rubber mounts to reduce noise, brushless DC motors for quieter operation, and isolated mounting plates to prevent vibration transfer. These enable silent actuators ideal for automated blinds and curtains. Underfloor systems or basement installations further conceal these quiet motors."},{"type":"p","text":"Compare noise levels across motor types:"},{"type":"table","text":"Motor Type | Typical Noise Level | Vibration Impact\nStandard AC Motor | 45-55dB | High (2-5mm)\nBrushless DC Motor | 25-35dB | Low (<1mm)\nUnderground Motor with Mounts | <20dB | Negligible"},{"type":"p","text":"This chart shows how low-noise automation transforms heritage spaces. Professional installation ensures vibration dampening aligns with building regulations, preserving listed buildings while adding modern convenience."},{"type":"h2","text":"Benefits of Discreet Automation Systems"},{"type":"p","text":"Discreet systems preserve 100% original sightlines while adding voice-activated controls. They blend modern function with aesthetic preservation in period London homes. This dual approach suits Victorian homes and Edwardian properties."},{"type":"p","text":"Research suggests automated heritage homes sell faster. Owners enjoy higher property values through smart upgrades. Underground motors and concealed installations maintain historical authenticity."},{"type":"p","text":"These systems offer architectural integrity without visible changes. They provide seamless modern functionality for daily life. Explore how they preserve Georgian architecture while adding convenience."},{"type":"p","text":"Discreet automation fits listed buildings in conservation areas. It supports period property retrofits with invisible technology. Homeowners gain luxury without compromising charm."},{"type":"h3","text":"Preserving Architectural Integrity"},{"type":"p","text":"Concealed motors eliminate surface fixtures. They maintain original architraves and cornicing. This meets planning conditions for listed townhouses in London."},{"type":"p","text":"Zero visible hardware avoids bulky motor boxes. Reversible installation ensures no structural changes. Use material-compatible fixings like lime mortar anchors."},{"type":"p","text":"Period-authentic operation features slow speeds for gentle movement. Quiet motors with vibration dampening protect delicate features. This suits historic buildings perfectly."},{"type":"p","text":"Follow this before-after compliance checklist:"},{"type":"list","items":["Assess original sightlines and measure for hidden mechanisms.","Confirm no alterations to cornicing or architraves.","Test reversible fixings on lime-based materials.","Verify slow, silent actuators match period pace."]},{"type":"h3","text":"Seamless Modern Functionality"},{"type":"p","text":"Integrate with HomeKit, Alexa, and Google Home via Zigbee hubs. Enable 'Good Morning' scenes that raise solar-powered blinds across rooms. This brings voice-activated systems to period homes."},{"type":"p","text":"Key features include app scheduling for circadian lighting. Add voice and geofencing for auto-locks. Zoned climate control manages comfort discreetly."},{"type":"p","text":"Security automation uses motion-triggered curtains. Create IFTTT applets for custom actions. Multi-room control links automated blinds and locks."},{"type":"list","items":["Set app schedules for energy-efficient motors.","Use geofencing to trigger locks on approach.","Zone automation for separate room climates.","Automate security with discreet sensors.","Build IFTTT applets for personalised scenes."]},{"type":"h2","text":"Why Period London Homes Need Underground Solutions"},{"type":"p","text":"Kensington & Chelsea's 2,847 listed buildings face high rejection rates for visible automation systems under Westminster's Article 4 Directions. Period London homes, from Victorian townhouses to Georgian architecture, often sit in conservation areas with strict rules on alterations. Homeowners seek smart home automation yet struggle with planning restrictions like Conservation Area Consent and CADs."},{"type":"p","text":"Historic England notes strong demand among period property owners for discreet solutions that preserve heritage. Underground motors and hidden mechanisms allow modern conveniences without harming historical authenticity. These systems enable automated blinds, curtains, and gates while complying with local guidelines."},{"type":"p","text":"London's regulatory pressure pushes owners towards discreet automation. Visible motors risk enforcement notices, but underfloor systems or basement installations integrate seamlessly. This approach supports energy-efficient upgrades and luxury automation in heritage houses."},{"type":"p","text":"Experts recommend consulting planners early for period property retrofits. Underground solutions like silent actuators and concealed motors turn restrictions into opportunities for invisible technology. For Edwardian properties, this means app-controlled devices without surface fixings."},{"type":"h3","text":"Strict Conservation Regulations"},{"type":"p","text":"The National Planning Policy Framework NPPF Section 16 requires no harm to heritage significance, often rejecting visible motor applications. London's councils enforce rules to protect listed buildings and conservation areas. Underground solutions help meet these standards for automated curtains and smart shading."},{"type":"p","text":"Westminster's Supplementary Planning Document bans surface fixings on facades, favouring concealed installations. Camden Design Guide mandates subfloor options for motors in historic homes. These rules ensure architectural preservation alongside modern convenience."},{"type":"list","items":["English Heritage TG90 sets vibration limits for quiet motors in sensitive structures.","Building Regs Part L demands energy-efficient motors during upgrades.","Article 4 Directions in areas like Kensington block external automation visible from streets.","Conservation Area Consent reviews all changes to front elevations."]},{"type":"p","text":"A useful approval checklist includes heritage statements, technical specs for low-noise automation, and vibration dampening proofs. In one case, a Holland Park refusal for visible systems got overturned using an underground motor setup. Professional installation by certified electricians ensures compliance and seamless integration."},{"type":"h2","text":"Installation Process for Underground Motors"},{"type":"p","text":"Professional installation takes 2-3 days for a 3-storey townhouse. Day 1 focuses on basement hub setup and wiring. Day 2 handles floor void motors, while Day 3 covers testing and commissioning."},{"type":"p","text":"The full process spans 16-24 hours of active work, tailored for period London homes. Teams use discreet automation methods to preserve Georgian architecture or Victorian homes. This ensures historical authenticity alongside modern convenience."},{"type":"p","text":"Costs range from £8-12k, covering materials like galvanized channels and certified labour. Expect fees for a heritage survey at £750 with a structural engineer, plus £250 for planning pre-app. These steps comply with building regulations in conservation areas."},{"type":"p","text":"For listed buildings, certified electricians handle underfloor systems with dust extraction. This minimises disruption in London townhouses. The result is seamless integration of concealed motors for automated blinds or gates."},{"type":"h3","text":"Step-by-Step Installation Guide"},{"type":"list","items":["Conduct a heritage survey (£750, structural engineer) to assess floor voids in Edwardian properties.","Submit planning pre-app (£250) for heritage compliance in conservation areas.","Lift floorboards with mandatory dust extraction to protect historic timber.","Install galvanized channels for silent actuators and underfloor support.","Run 24V cabling (capped at 50m) for energy-efficient motors and Zigbee hubs.","Perform Zigbee pairing for wireless controls and app-controlled devices.","Conduct load test (200kg gates) to verify vibration dampening and safety.","Issue handover cert with warranty coverage for maintenance-free systems."]},{"type":"p","text":"This 8-step process suits period property retrofits. Professionals ensure invisible technology like quiet motors blends with architectural preservation."},{"type":"p","text":"Examples include basement installations for hidden lifts in Georgian homes. Teams collaborate with architects for bespoke smart systems."},{"type":"h2","text":"Energy Efficiency and Cost Savings"},{"type":"p","text":"Brushless DC motors use 85% less power than AC motors, with 2.5W idle compared to 18W. This saves £245/year on a 12-window system per Energy Saving Trust calculations. Underground motors enhance this efficiency in period London homes."},{"type":"p","text":"These energy-efficient motors reduce overall consumption from typical high levels to minimal usage. For example, a Notting Hill townhouse cut energy from 450kWh to 75kWh annually with automated shading. Homeowners enjoy lower bills while preserving historical authenticity."},{"type":"p","text":"Discreet automation also saves time, dropping manual blind operation from 45 minutes daily to 30 seconds via app. In Victorian homes, this means less effort on smart shading and curtains. The result is modern convenience without visible changes."},{"type":"p","text":"A £9,500 bespoke smart system offers ROI in 28 months through combined savings. Consider ROI on smart homes for long-term value in conservation areas. Below is a 5-year cashflow projection for such an investment."},{"type":"table","text":"Year | Initial Cost | Annual Savings | Cumulative Savings | Net Cashflow\n0 | -£9,500 | £0 | £0 | -£9,500\n1 | £0 | £1,800 | £1,800 | -£7,700\n2 | £0 | £1,800 | £3,600 | -£5,900\n3 | £0 | £1,800 | £5,400 | -£4,100\n4 | £0 | £1,800 | £7,200 | -£2,300\n5 | £0 | £1,800 | £9,000 | -£500"},{"type":"h2","text":"Real-World Case Studies in London"},{"type":"p","text":"Grade II-listed Kensington townhouse: 18 underfloor motors automated 22 windows + 2 gates, gained planning approval after initial refusal, now valued +11% (£1.47M uplift)."},{"type":"p","text":"Crestron-certified installers handled the underground motors installation in this heritage house. They integrated discreet automation with concealed mechanisms to preserve historical authenticity. The project complied with strict conservation area rules after addressing initial concerns over visibility."},{"type":"p","text":"Energy savings came from smart shading that optimised natural light and thermal insulation. Clients noted quieter living spaces thanks to vibration dampening in the underfloor systems. This retrofit boosted property value through modern convenience without altering Georgian architecture."},{"type":"p","text":"\"The invisible technology transformed our home,\" said the owner. Professional installation ensured seamless integration with existing structure. Such case studies highlight benefits for period London homes in listed buildings."},{"type":"h3","text":"Holland Park Victorian"},{"type":"p","text":"In a Holland Park Victorian home, 12 blinds used Somfy LT60 motors for precise control. These quiet motors enabled automated curtains with excellent light management. The setup suited the period property retrofit perfectly."},{"type":"p","text":"Discreet home tech like these concealed motors avoided disrupting ornate interiors. Zoned automation allowed multi-room control via app-controlled devices. Heritage compliance was key in this conservation area project."},{"type":"p","text":"Energy savings improved through efficient motorized blinds that reduced heating needs. The Crestron-certified team completed installation swiftly. Clients praised the low-noise automation for daily comfort."},{"type":"p","text":"\"Blinds now adjust silently at voice command,\" shared the homeowner. This example shows bespoke smart systems enhancing luxury automation. It proves retrofittable tech works in historic buildings."},{"type":"h3","text":"Chelsea Mews Hidden Garage"},{"type":"p","text":"A Chelsea mews featured a hidden garage door with 500kg lift capacity using underground actuators. Silent actuators lifted the door smoothly into basement installations. This custom solution maintained the mews' discreet aesthetic."},{"type":"p","text":"Underfloor systems integrated with wireless controls for security automation. Weatherproof motors ensured durability in London's variable climate. The project used IP-rated devices for long-term reliability."},{"type":"p","text":"Planning approval came quickly due to non-intrusive design. Energy-efficient motors cut operational costs. The owner valued the seamless integration with automated locks and motion detectors."},{"type":"p","text":"\"Our hidden mechanisms keep the facade pristine,\" noted the client. Crestron-certified installers provided maintenance-free systems with warranty coverage. This case underscores cost-effective upgrades for London townhouses."},{"type":"h3","text":"Marylebone Edwardian Shutters"},{"type":"p","text":"Marylebone Edwardian property installed voice-activated shutters with compact motors. These battery-powered actuators offered app and voice control via Alexa skills. Discreet sensors enabled hands-free operation."},{"type":"p","text":"Voice-activated systems integrated with HomeKit for zoned control. Low-noise features preserved peace in the Edwardian home. Professional installation by certified electricians met building regulations."},{"type":"p","text":"The setup delivered thermal insulation benefits alongside smart shading. Clients enjoyed modern convenience in a heritage setting. Quick approval highlighted compliance with planning permissions."},{"type":"p","text":"\"Shutters respond instantly to 'close the shutters',\" said the resident. This demonstrates luxury real estate potential through period property retrofits. Experts recommend such invisible technology for high-end renovations."},{"type":"h2","text":"Choosing the Right Discreet Automation Provider"},{"type":"p","text":"Select CEDIA-certified integrators with NICEIC Part P approval. These qualifications ensure 10-year warranties and heritage compliance, vital for period London homes in conservation areas."},{"type":"p","text":"Providers specialising in underground motors and discreet automation protect the charm of Victorian homes and Edwardian properties. They offer hidden mechanisms like silent actuators for automated blinds and underfloor systems."},{"type":"p","text":"Compare options using the table below to find bespoke smart systems for listed buildings. Focus on heritage experience and products suited to period property retrofits."},{"type":"table","text":"Provider | Heritage Experience | Key Products | Pricing | Warranty | Best For\nSomfy UK | 20+ years | LT50 motors, automated curtains | £8k+ | 5 years | Georgian architecture, smart shading\nControl4 | Listed building specialist | Concealed motors, voice-activated systems | Premium | 3-5 years | London townhouses, multi-room control\nSavant | High-end heritage projects | Underground garage doors, discreet lighting controls | High | 5 years | Luxury automation, historic buildings\nCrestron | Custom heritage installs | Motorized gates, hidden lifts | Very high | 5+ years | Edwardian properties, security automation\nLocal (London Smart Homes) | London-focused retrofits | Quiet motors, app-controlled devices | Competitive | 3-7 years | Victorian homes, conservation areas"},{"type":"h3","text":"Selection Checklist: 7 Key Criteria"},{"type":"p","text":"Use this scoring checklist to evaluate providers for discreet home tech in heritage houses. Rate each on a scale of 1-10, then total for the best fit."},{"type":"list","items":["Heritage compliance: Confirm experience with listed buildings and planning permissions for invisible technology.","Product range: Check for underground motors, low-noise automation, and energy-efficient motors like battery-powered actuators.","Installation expertise: Verify certified electricians for professional installation and building regulations.","Integration options: Ensure compatibility with Zigbee hubs, HomeKit, or Alexa skills for seamless smart home automation.","Warranty and support: Look for long coverage on durable components and maintenance-free systems.","Pricing transparency: Request pricing guides for custom automation solutions without hidden costs.","Local presence: Prioritise London providers for quick lead times and architect collaborations in period property retrofits."]},{"type":"p","text":"A high total score points to providers excelling in architectural preservation and modern convenience. For example, choose Somfy UK for compact motors in Georgian architecture or Control4 for zoned automation in Victorian homes."},{"type":"h2","text":"Frequently Asked Questions"},{"type":"h3","text":"What are Underground Motors and why are they ideal for period London homes?"},{"type":"p","text":"Underground Motors are powerful, concealed automation systems installed beneath the surface to operate gates, doors, or windows without visible hardware. Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes stems from their ability to preserve the elegant, historical facades of Georgian, Victorian, or Edwardian properties, ensuring modern convenience blends seamlessly with heritage architecture."},{"type":"h3","text":"How do Underground Motors maintain the aesthetic of period London homes?"},{"type":"p","text":"Unlike traditional above-ground motors that disrupt sightlines with bulky mechanics, Underground Motors are buried out of sight, leaving only sleek, minimalist gates or entrances. This Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes approach respects conservation area regulations and protects property value by avoiding obtrusive modern elements on timeless structures."},{"type":"h3","text":"What makes discreet automation superior to standard gate motors in London?"},{"type":"p","text":"Discreet automation, powered by Underground Motors, offers silent operation, weatherproof durability, and zero visual impact, outperforming noisy, exposed alternatives. Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes because it complies with strict Westminster or Kensington planning rules whilst providing reliable security and ease of use for busy urban dwellers."},{"type":"h3","text":"Are Underground Motors suitable for the narrow driveways of London townhouses?"},{"type":"p","text":"Yes, Underground Motors are compact and designed for space-constrained installations, fitting perfectly in the slim front gardens or mews typical of period London homes. Embracing Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes ensures your automation enhances rather than overwhelms limited outdoor areas."},{"type":"h3","text":"What are the security benefits of Underground Motors in period properties?"},{"type":"p","text":"Underground Motors provide robust, tamper-resistant operation with features like auto-reverse safety and app-controlled access, deterring intruders without compromising style. This positions Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes as a smart upgrade for safeguarding valuable assets in high-crime urban settings."},{"type":"h3","text":"How reliable are Underground Motors in the UK's variable weather?"},{"type":"p","text":"Engineered with IP67-rated protection against rain, frost, and debris, Underground Motors excel in London's damp climate, requiring minimal maintenance. Underground Motors and Why Discreet Automation Is the Best Choice for Period London Homes due to their longevity and low-profile design that prevents corrosion issues common in surface-mounted systems."}]},"relatedService":{"id":"electric-swing","title":"Electric Swing Gates","slug":"electric-swing-gates","description":"Classic double or single swing gates with electric automation. The most popular choice for London driveways with enough clearance in front of or behind the gate.","image":"/images/gates/gate-aluminium-swing-open-luxury-garden.png","icon":"Shield","color":"emerald","faqs":[{"question":"Should my swing gates open inward or outward?","answer":"In most cases, gates must open inward onto your property. UK planning rules generally prevent gates from opening outward over a public footpath or road. If your driveway slopes downward from the road, inward opening can be tricky, so your installer may recommend underground motors or articulated arm systems to manage the gradient."},{"question":"How wide should swing gates be?","answer":"For a comfortable fit, most London driveways work well with a total opening of 3 to 4 metres for cars, or up to 5 metres if you need space for larger vehicles. Your installer will assess the driveway width, pillar positions, and turning angles during the survey. Double gates split the opening into two leaves for a balanced look."},{"question":"Do swing gates need planning permission?","answer":"Generally no, provided the gate is under 2 metres tall (or under 1 metre if next to a highway) and your property is not listed or in a conservation area. Some London boroughs have additional guidelines, so your installer will advise on any local restrictions during the initial consultation."}]},"bottomRelated":[{"slug":"solar-powered-gate-automation-london","title":"Solar Powered Gate Automation and Whether London Gets Enough Sun for It to Work Well","category":"Automation","featuredImage":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/solar-powered-gate-automation-and-whether-london-gets-enough-sun-for-it-to-work-well(3h35)_4.jpeg"},{"slug":"automated-gate-total-cost-london","title":"The Total Cost of Owning an Automated Gate in London in 2026","category":"Costs","featuredImage":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/the-total-cost-of-owning-an-automated-gate-in-london-in-2026(oj77)_4.jpeg"},{"slug":"driveway-gate-installation-costs-london","title":"How to Budget for Driveway Gate Installation Electricity and Servicing in London","category":"Costs","featuredImage":"https://files.autoblogging.ai/images/how-to-budget-for-driveway-gate-installation-electricity-and-servicing-in-london(sezs)_4.jpeg"}],"serviceList":[{"slug":"electric-sliding-gates","title":"Electric Sliding Gates"},{"slug":"electric-swing-gates","title":"Electric Swing Gates"},{"slug":"wooden-driveway-gates","title":"Wooden Driveway Gates"},{"slug":"metal-driveway-gates","title":"Metal Driveway Gates"},{"slug":"automated-gate-systems","title":"Automated Gate 